[2] China: National Health Commission 4 Apr 2020; 81 669 total cases, 3329 deaths
Date: Sat 4 Apr 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqfkdt/202004/4f4e36d54fc941d48f6ce6554514075e.shtml


From 0 to 24:00 on [4 Apr 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 30 newly diagnosed cases, of which 25 cases were imported cases from abroad and 5 were local cases (5 cases in Guangdong). There were 3 additional deaths (3 cases in Hubei); 11 new suspected cases were imported from abroad.

On the same day, 213 new cases were discharged, 1869 close contacts were released from medical observation, and the condition of 36 cases was downgraded from serious.

There are 697 confirmed imported cases (including 18 severe cases), and 107 suspected cases. A total of 913 cases were diagnosed, 216 cases recovered and were discharged, and 0 cases [among the imported cases] died.

As of 24:00 on [4 Apr 2020], according to the reports of 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there are 1376 confirmed cases (295 severe cases). A total of 76 964 cases recovered and were discharged, and 3329 deaths were reported. A total of 81 669 confirmed cases and 107 suspected cases have been reported. A total of 713 110 close contacts have been traced, and 17 436 close contacts are still under medical observation.

There were 0 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (0 cases in Wuhan), 183 newly recovered and discharged cases (all in Wuhan), 3 new deaths (all in Wuhan), 648 confirmed cases (644 cases in Wuhan), There were 267 severe cases (264 cases in Wuhan). A total of 63 945 patients recovered and were discharged (46 794 in Wuhan), a total of 3210 deaths were reported (2570 cases in Wuhan), and 67 803 cases were confirmed (50 008 cases in Wuhan). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 cases in Wuhan) and 0 existing suspected cases (0 cases in Wuhan).

31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 47 new cases of asymptomatic infections, including 16 cases of asymptomatic infections imported from abroad; 3 cases of confirmed cases on the same day (3 imported cases from abroad); 50 [new] cases are under medical observation (8 imported from abroad). There are still 1024 cases of asymptomatic infections in medical observation (244 cases imported from abroad).

A total of 1261 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 862 cases in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (186 discharged and 4 deaths), 44 cases in the Macau Special Administrative Region (10 discharged), and 355 cases in Taiwan (50 discharged and 5 deaths).

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the report above, a total of 81 669 confirmed cases of COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, including 3329 deaths, representing an increase of 30 cases and 3 deaths in the 24 hours since the last report was prepared. Out of the 30 new cases, 25 were imported while 5 occurred as a result of local transmission. In addition, 3 deaths were reported, all from Hubei. 17 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, and Macau reported 1 newly confirmed case in the past 24 hours.

A total of 25 newly confirmed cases were imported cases into China. Origins of importation were not available but the total number of imported cases is now increasing, which presents a challenge for the Chinese public health authorities to identify the infections in imported cases, contact tracing, and prevent emergence of new clusters of community transmission.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7184654,155. - Mod.UBA]

