[In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 81 cases and 6 deaths. A total of 10 237 confirmed cases, including 183 deaths were reported today, up from 10 156 cases and 177 deaths yesterday [3 Apr 2020]. The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 14 consecutive days.

